cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CY, cs.SOC, cs.HC 

This paper discusses the dynamics of collective attention among a large population, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI). The analysis of the data from an interactive website also involves data mining and machine learning techniques, which could be categorized under cs.SD (data science). The study also touches upon the psychology of human behavior and decision-making, which could be classified under cs.CY (computational psychology). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of novelty on attention, which could be relevant to the sub-categories of social computing (cs.SOC) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
